**OpenAI Tips**

**What can I do to prevent my OpenAI credits from running out quickly?**
Pay attention to the following points:
* Be sure to log the requests you send to the AI. You can use free services like Logfire or similar services for this purpose.
* Make sure your assistant does not get stuck in an infinite loop and talk to the judge indefinitely.
* It's a good idea to set up a mechanism so that if the TCP connection with the competition judge is terminated (the request is canceled), you also stop the ongoing processes of your assistant.

**What should I do if my OpenAI credit runs out?**
Based on our assessment, the provided credit is sufficient for 10 tests by the judge and your local tests. However, if your credit runs out, you can submit your request by contacting the competition support via Telegram at @torobTurbo. (To maintain fairness in the competition, we will either give credit to everyone or to no one.)

